      "rationale": "Three mesh refinements performed (coarse 0.8 mm, medium 0.5 mm, fine 0.3 mm global element size at screw-rod interface). Stiffness QoI changed by 1.4% between medium and fine meshes; GCI = 3.1%. Medium mesh adopted for all production runs. Discretization error assessed at Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residual norms converge to <1e-6 relative; energy balance error <0.1% at each load step.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear solver (Newton-Raphson with automatic time-stepping) converged to residual norm 8.3e-8 in all 11 production runs. Energy balance error remained below 0.04% across all load steps. Solver error contribution to total numerical uncertainty estimated at <0.3% of QoI."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
