      "rationale": "Simulation setup was independently reviewed by a second FDA OSEL engineer against a documented 24-item checklist covering geometry import, material assignment, contact definition, boundary conditions, and load application. One minor discrepancy (incorrect friction coefficient for rod-screw interface) was identified and corrected prior to production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification that continuum elastic-plastic constitutive model with frictional contact is appropriate for the compression-bending regime of interest.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V ELI pedicle screw and rod modeled as elastic-plastic (bilinear isotropic hardening, E=114 GPa, σ_y=880 MPa, E_t=1.14 GPa) consistent with ASTM F136 coupon data. Frictional contact (μ=0.2, augmented Lagrange) captures screw-rod locking behavior observed experimentally. Model form uncertainty estimated via sensitivity to friction coefficient (±0.05) yielding <1.8% QoI variation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric dimensions sourced from traceable measurements; uncertainty propagation documented.",
      "rationale": "Screw and rod geometry digitized from CMM measurements of production hardware (dimensional tolerance ±0.01 mm). Material properties from lot-specific tensile coupon testing (n=3 per lot). Monte Carlo uncertainty propagation (n=1000 samples) over material and geometric input distributions yields combined input uncertainty of 2.1% on stiffness QoI, incorporated into validation metric uval."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 constructs tested; samples drawn from production lots with documented traceability; dimensional inspection performed on tested hardware.",
      "rationale": "Eleven constructs assembled from production-lot hardware (5 screws and 1 rod per construct). Each screw and rod dimensionally inspected post-assembly (CMM, 100% inspection). Lot traceability documented. Sample size of 11 provides 90% confidence interval on mean stiffness of ±4.2%, adequate for the <10% acceptance bound."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must replicate the full range of loading rates and environmental conditions relevant to the COU; minimum two independent test configurations required.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single quasi-static displacement rate (5 mm/min) per ASTM F1717 protocol. No variation in loading rate or temperature was explored. This single test condition is a recognized limitation; the achieved level of 2 is below the required level of 3. The shortfall is documented and accepted by the regulatory team given the quasi-static nature of the clinical loading scenario and the conservative nature of the F1717 protocol."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation inputs demonstrably derived from or equivalent to test-article measurements; no uncontrolled surrogates used.",
      "rationale": "Simulation geometry and material inputs derived directly from CMM and coupon measurements of the specific hardware used in testing. No surrogate or literature-default values substituted. Cross-laboratory equivalency confirmed by blind exchange of five constructs between laboratories, yielding <2% inter-laboratory stiffness difference."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation metric E/uval < 1.96 for all primary QoIs; QoI difference < 10%.",
      "rationale": "Three QoIs evaluated: construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement. E/uval values: 1.41 (stiffness), 1.18 (yield force), 1.63 (force at 40 mm). All below 1.96 threshold. Maximum QoI difference: 7.3% (yield force). All acceptance criteria satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs validated in the validation activity must be the same QoIs used in the regulatory submission claim.",
      "rationale": "The three QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are identical to those specified in the 510(k) submission claim and in the ASTM F1717 acceptance criteria. No surrogate QoIs used. Direct correspondence between validation and submission QoIs confirmed by the regulatory affairs team."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
